  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Bosnia and Herzegovina: Enhancing Social Cohesion in Communities Hosting People on the Move</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project responds to the increase of tensions and anti-migrant sentiments in local communities in Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) that are hosting large numbers of migrants, asylum-seekers and refugees, in particular in the areas around Sarajevo and in Una Sana Canton. The project aims to establish a dialogue between migration management actors, local community representatives, central government stakeholders, common citizens and representatives of the migrant and refugee community and find solutions to address the main causes of these tensions. This project will also continue the work initiated through a previous project to reduce the risk of and control COVID-19 infections among people on the move and will be complemented by interventions aimed at caring for the mental well-being of this population. Ultimately, the project aims to contribute to enhance social cohesion in communities hosting refugees and migrants and enable a response to the migration emergency that benefits people on the move and BiH citizens alike.</narrative>
  </description>
